---
import LegalLayout from '../components/legal/LegalLayout.astro';
import LegalSection from '../components/legal/LegalSection.astro';
---
<LegalLayout title="Privacy Notice | NozzleNote by BMR" description="Preliminary privacy notice for NozzleNote by BMR, including current conditional GA4 website analytics disclosure and planned local-first app data direction." eyebrow="Privacy notice" heading="Privacy Notice — preliminary, with current website analytics disclosure." intro="This notice is preliminary and will need review before public app release or commercial availability. GA4 website analytics may be active when a valid measurement ID is configured." currentPath="/privacy/">
  <LegalSection title="Current website data collection"><p>This static website does not provide accounts, checkout, support forms, newsletter forms, app downloads, license activation, cloud sync, or mobile app features. It does not intentionally collect names, emails, printer records, maintenance records, payment data, license data, or support messages through site forms.</p></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Google Analytics 4"><p>When PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID is configured with a valid ID, the website loads standard Google Analytics 4 for basic website measurement. GA4 may measure page views, traffic sources, referrers, scroll behavior, outbound clicks, and general engagement. The GA4 script is conditional and is not rendered when the measurement ID is missing or invalid.</p><p>No custom analytics events containing personal data are configured. Names, emails, printer records, maintenance records, license data, payment data, support messages, and user-submitted personal content should not be sent to GA4.</p></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Analytics limits"><ul><li>No advertising, remarketing, Google Signals, User-ID tracking, Google Ads linking, custom dimensions, e-commerce tracking, manual link-click instrumentation, form instrumentation, or manual personal-data collection has been added.</li><li>A future cookie or analytics consent layer should allow visitors to accept, reject, or manage non-essential analytics cookies where required.</li><li>Website browsing is not described as private by default. That language is reserved for planned app maintenance records and local-first app data.</li></ul></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Local-first app data direction"><p>NozzleNote by BMR is being developed with app maintenance records planned to stay local by default. Public app behavior, backups, exports, account features, license activation, cloud sync, mobile app functionality, and support workflows are not final and should be documented before release.</p></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Future or conditional data categories"><p>Future app, account, license, payment, support, cloud, mobile, catalog, or campaign features may require additional data categories and reviewed privacy language before launch. Contact placeholder: [insert contact email before production launch].</p></LegalSection>
</LegalLayout>
